comments.message:
I know I suggested this behaviour initially, but on reflection I don't think we want to bake expectation of this behaviour into the new API. We can't fix it once we do TIDs properly. Rather, users of libpldm should initialise the mappings themselves if this is what they desire. For example, the user of libpldm can do the following when first setting up the transport:

```c
for (int i = 0; i <= PLDM_TID_MAX; i++) {
    rc = pldm_transport_af_mctp_map_tid(af_mctp, (pldm_tid_t)i, i);
    if (rc) { ... }
}
```

Then here we just drop the message if there's no mapping in place.
